# Note Taker Application

A dynamic note-taking application designed to write, save, and delete notes. This application aids users in organizing thoughts and tracking tasks efficiently.

## Table of Contents

- [Description](#description)
- [Acceptance Criteria](#acceptance-criteria)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Installation](#installation-and-launch)
- [License](#license)

## Description

Start by launching the Note Taker to be greeted with a landing page. This page features a link that directs users straight to the notes page.

## Acceptance Criteria

### Landing Page
- Presented with a welcoming landing page containing a link to the notes page.

### Notes Page Access
- Display of existing notes on the left-hand side.
- Empty fields on the right-hand side await your new note title and content.

### New Note Creation
- As you type, the "Save Note" and "Clear Form" buttons materialize in the top navigation.

### Saving Notes
- Clicking the "Save Note" button commits your note, displaying it among other notes on the left.
- Post-saving, the "Save Note" and "Clear Form" buttons retreat from the navigation.

### Viewing Existing Notes
- A simple click on an existing note reveals its content on the right.
- For new notes, a "New Note" button pops up in the top navigation.

### Crafting Additional Notes
- The "New Note" button in the navigation prompts empty fields, ready for your next note's title and content.
- Once activated, the "New Note" button discreetly vanishes.

## Usage

Crafted for users who juggle a multitude of information, this application grants rapid access to old notes while making new note creation a breeze.

## Installation and Launch

1. Obtain the repository by either cloning or downloading.
2. Install any required dependencies.
3. Fire up the application and embark on your note-taking journey!

